# Always Latest Docs

Library APIs change. Every research note `WebFetch`es the official docs of every dependency it introduces and records the page title + URL + retrieval timestamp. Citations older than 14 days fail validation.

## Do

- `WebFetch` (or open in browser, then paste URL) the live docs page for every new dependency.
- Record: page title + full URL + retrieval date in the note's citations table.
- Re-fetch and bump the date if a citation ages past 14 days.
- Lock versions via `pnpm ls --depth=0` after CLI install — never hand-write a version.

## Don't

- Cite "latest" without a date.
- Type a version from memory (e.g. `"nestjs-zod": "^5.3.0"`) — let the CLI write it.
- Reuse a citation older than 14 days without re-verifying.

## Concrete example

| Topic | Title | URL | Retrieved |
|-------|-------|-----|-----------|
| nestjs-zod | nestjs-zod v5.3.0 on npm | https://www.npmjs.com/package/nestjs-zod | 2026-05-12 |

